Embodiments are described with reference to the following figures, in which:
Figure 1 depicts a system including a mobile device operating to control a media player device, according to a non-limiting embodiment;
Figure 2 depicts a method of controlling the media player device of Figure 1 to play back media, according to a non-limiting embodiment;
Figure 3 depicts a variation of the system of Figure 1, according to a non-limiting embodiment;
Figure 4 depicts an example of a database stored by the mobile device of Figure 3, according to a non-limiting embodiment; and
Figure 5 depicts a method of controlling the media player device of Figure 3 to play back media, according to a non-limiting embodiment.

claim.claim-text:
A mobile device (104), comprising:
a network interface (136);
a memory (116) storing first audio data and second audio data;
a microphone (132); and
a processor (112) interconnected with the network interface (136), the memory (116) and the microphone (132), the processor (112) operating to:
transmit, to a media player device (108) via the network interface (136), a request to initiate a connection between the mobile device (104) and the media player device (108);
send the first audio data over the connection to the media player device (108) for playback by the media player device (108);
detect the playback of the first audio data via the microphone (132); and
in response to detecting playback of the first audio data, send the second audio data over the connection to the player device for playback by the media player device (108).

A method in a mobile device (104) having a processor (112) interconnected with a network interface (136), a memory (116) and a microphone (132), the method comprising:
storing first audio data and second audio data in the memory (116);
transmitting, from the processor (112) to a media player device (108) via the network interface (136), a request to initiate a connection between the mobile device (104) and the media player device (108);
sending the first audio data over the connection to the media player device (108) for playback by the player device;
detecting, at the processor (112), the playback of the first audio data via the microphone (132); and
in response to detecting playback of the first audio data, sending the second audio data over the connection to the media player device (108) for playback by the media player device (108).

A computer-readable medium storing a plurality of computer-readable instructions executable by a processor (112) of a mobile device (104) having a network interface (136), a memory (116) and a microphone (132) interconnected with the processor (112), for performing a method comprising:
storing first audio data and second audio data in the memory (116);
transmitting, from the processor (112) to a media player device (108) via the network interface (136), a request to initiate a connection between the mobile device (104) and the media player device (108);
sending the first audio data over the connection to the media player device (108) for playback by the player device;
detecting, at the processor (112), the playback of the first audio data via the microphone (132); and
in response to detecting playback of the first audio data, sending the second audio data over the connection to the media player device (108) for playback by the media player device (108).
